ong%3EProductivity%20worries%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20no%20consensus%20on%20whether%20a%20full%20RTO%20is%20%26quot%3Bbetter%26quot%3B%20than%20hybrid%20or%20entirely%20remote%20roles.%20Bosses%20demanding%20that%20workers%20show%20up%20more%20in%20person%20often%20cite%20a%20desire%20to%20maintain%20culture%2C%20spur%20innovation%2C%20and%20foster%20collaboration.%20Some%20point%20to%20concerns%20about%20productivity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENicole%20Kyle%2C%20who%20researches%20the%20future%20of%20work%2C%20said%20that%20IRL%20work%20doesn't%20actually%20guarantee%20increased%20productivity%20and%20performance.%20However%2C%20these%20metrics%20can%20go%20up%20when%20employers%20allow%20for%20more%20remote%20or%20hybrid%20setups%2C%20said%20Kyle%2C%20who's%20cofounder%20of%20CMP%20Research%2C%20in%20part%20because%20workers%20feel%20more%20autonomy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNothing%20is%20less%20engaging%20to%20employees%20than%20not%20having%20flexibility%20and%20choice%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGallup%20notes%20that%20full-time%20remote%20or%20hybrid%20workers%20tend%20to%20have%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gallup.com%2F401384%2Findicator-hybrid-work.aspx%23ite-510899%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esignificantly%20higher%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20engagement%20than%20on-site%20workers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20so%2C%20there%20are%20times%20when%20being%20in%20the%20workplace%20makes%20sense%2C%20said%20Lisa%20Walker%2C%20a%20managing%20partner%20at%20the%20executive%20search%20firm%20DHR%20Global.%20She%20told%20BI%20that%20for%20roles%20like%20those%20in%20operations%20or%20where%20there's%20a%20short-term%20deadline%2C%20remote%20work%20can%20present%20challenges.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20want%20to%20walk%20down%20the%20hall.%20You%20need%20an%20answer.%20You%20need%20to%20react%2C%26quot%3B%20Walker%20said.%20That's%20harder%20on%20Slack.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2205438429-9bdb-4da3-bc24-559d2cb0e428%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EGoing%20off%20on%20your%20own%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EA%20decade%20ago%2C%20after%20years%20spent%20working%20in%20offices%20at%20big%20agencies%2C%20Curtis%20Sparrer%20cofounded%20a%20fully%20remote%20PR%20and%20marketing%20firm.%20Too%20often%2C%20he%20said%2C%20startups%20had%20to%20choose%20between%20paying%20rent%20or%20making%20payroll.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20said%2C%20'What%20if%20we%20never%20had%20to%20make%20that%20choice%3F'%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESparrer%20and%20his%20business%20partner%20have%20grown%20the%20firm%2C%20called%20Bospar%2C%20to%20about%2070%20people.%20In%20the%20early%20days%2C%20the%20company%20relied%20on%20conference%20calls%20and%20text%20messages%20to%20keep%20workers%20connected.%20Now%2C%20it%20uses%20tools%20like%20Slack%20and%20video%20calls.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20firm's%20productivity%20isn't%20a%20worry%2C%20Sparrer%20said%2C%20because%20workers%20are%20in%20frequent%20contact%20with%20each%20other.%20If%20someone%20does%20slack%20off%2C%20managers%20will%20address%20it%2C%20he%20said.%20Otherwise%2C%20he%20sees%20the%20quiet%20of%20home%20as%20a%20boon%20to%20productivity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20it%20comes%20to%20thoughtful%2C%20focused%20work%2C%20nothing%20beats%20work%20from%20home%20because%20that's%20the%20way%20you%20cut%20down%20on%20distractions%2C%26quot%3B%20Sparrer%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20help%20keep%20workers%20connected%2C%20the%20firm%20occasionally%20brings%20people%20together%20in%20person%2C%20though%20not%20to%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20want%20to%20do%20all%20the%20cultural%20things%2C%20but%20they%20absolutely%20do%20not%20want%20to%20work%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20That's%20because%20the%20firm's%20employees%20report%20they%20do%20better%20work%20independently.%20So%2C%20they%20instead%20use%20in-person%20gatherings%20to%20connect%20with%20colleagues.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a0ff7cbd-e27a-492e-8639-5cef679993ce%5C%22%3EFocus%20on%20output%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDeborah%20Perry%20Piscione%2C%20cofounder%20of%20Work3%20Institute%20and%20coauthor%20of%20the%20forthcoming%20book%20%26quot%3BEmployment%20is%20Dead%2C%26quot%3B%20told%20BI%20that%20focusing%20on%20output%20rather%20than%20where%20the%20job%20gets%20done%20can%20be%20savvy%20for%20employers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20don't%20understand%20what%20the%20fear%20is.%20At%20the%20end%20of%20the%20day%2C%20this%20is%20not%20about%20control.%20It's%20about%20output%20and%20productivity%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPiscione%20said%20that%20early%20in%20her%20career%2C%20working%20in%20Washington%2C%20DC%2C%20there%20was%20an%20expectation%20that%20employees%20should%20be%20at%20their%20desks%20from%208%20a.m.%20to%206%20p.m.%2C%20no%20matter%20what.%20She%20said%20she%20never%20understood%20why%20she%20had%20to%20stick%20around%20if%20she%20was%20more%20efficient%20or%20skipped%20lunch%20to%20wrap%20up%20her%20work%20early.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIncreasingly%2C%20Piscione%20said%2C%20employers%20and%20employees%20need%20to%20view%20work%20as%20a%20partnership.%20That's%20especially%20important%20in%20the%20face%20of%20technology%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fworkers-see-ai-automation-increasing-productivity-job-flexibility-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eartificial%20intelligence%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20could%20eliminate%20roles%20or%20rejigger%20how%20people%20do%20their%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBesides%2C%20she%20said%2C%20workers%20have%20more%20ways%20of%20getting%20by%20than%20only%20a%20few%20years%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20in%20this%20hyper%2C%20super%20gig%20economy%20where%20I%20don't%20have%20to%20take%20your%20crap%20anymore%2C%26quot%3B%20Piscione%20said%2C%20referring%20to%20overbearing%20employers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20Janielle%2C%20the%20globe-hopping%20marketer%20who%20describes%20herself%20as%20an%20older%20millennial%2C%20an%20additional%20remote%20job%20looked%20enticing%3A%20chief%20nomad%20officer.%20She%20applied%20for%20and%20got%20the%20role%20at%20Shift%2C%20which%20makes%20a%20web%20browser%20aimed%20at%20boosting%20productivity.%20The%20goal%20of%20her%20work%20is%20to%20demonstrate%20that%20it's%20possible%20to%20get%20a%20lot%20done%20from%20anywhere%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJanielle%20said%20she%20enjoys%20showcasing%20what's%20doable.%20She's%20been%20to%20some%2045%20countries%20and%20said%20the%20more%20she%20travels%2C%20the%20more%20she%20meets%20others%20who%20are%20succeeding%20outside%20the%20office%20without%20sacrificing%20productivity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20still%20a%20lot%20of%20space%20in%20the%20economy%20for%20these%20remote%20workers%20to%20thrive%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDo%20you%20have%20something%20to%20share%20about%20remote%20work%3F%20Business%20Insider%20would%20like%20to%20hear%20from%20you.%20Email%20our%20workplace%20team%20from%20a%20nonwork%20device%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Athegrind%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3Ethegrind%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20with%20your%20story%2C%20or%20ask%20for%20one%20of%20our%20reporter's%20Signal%20numbers.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fremote-work-means-considering-changing-jobs-amid-rto-wfh-debate-2025-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1736074022000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67784a3a9de00e389eb4531e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fremote-work-means-considering-changing-jobs-amid-rto-wfh-debate-2025-1%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Remote%20roles%20are%20dwindling%20for%20some%20workers%20as%20big%20companies%20recall%20employees.%20To%20work%20remotely%2C%20you%20might%20