ntic.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWinter%20storm%20warnings%20have%20been%20issued%20from%20western%20Kansas%20to%20the%20coastal%20states%20of%20Maryland%2C%20Delaware%20and%20Virginia%2C%20an%20unusually%20broad%201%2C500-mile%20(2%2C400-kilometer)%20swath%20under%20immediate%20threat.%20%26quot%3BDisruptive%20winter%20storm%20to%20impact%20the%20Central%20Plains%20to%20the%20Mid-Atlantic%20through%20Monday%20with%20widespread%20heavy%20snow%20and%20damaging%20ice%20accumulations%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20NWS%20said%20in%20its%20latest%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20agency%20warned%20that%20areas%20from%20northeastern%20Kansas%20to%20north-central%20Missouri%20would%20see%20%26quot%3Bthe%20heaviest%20snowfall%20in%20a%20decade.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EHistorically%20Low%20Temperatures%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20forecasters%2C%20a%20polar%20vortex%2C%20an%20area%20of%20cold%20air%20that%20circulates%20around%20the%20Arctic%2C%20is%20the%20reason%20behind%20the%20extreme%20weather%20conditions.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20some%2C%20this%20could%20be%20the%20heaviest%20snowfall%20in%20over%20a%20decade%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20National%20Oceanic%20and%20Atmospheric%20Administration%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20could%20lead%20to%20the%20coldest%20January%20for%20the%20US%20since%202011%2C%26quot%3B%20AccuWeather%20forecaster%20Dan%20DePodwin%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20%26quot%3Btemperatures%20that%20are%20well%20below%20historical%20average%26quot%3B%20could%20linger%20for%20a%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20the%20jet%20stream%20diving%20southward%2C%20temperatures%20are%20expected%20to%20plunge%2C%20in%20some%20places%20to%20below%20zero%20degrees%20Fahrenheit%20(-18%20Celsius)%2C%20while%20strong%20wind%20gusts%20will%20compound%20the%20dangers.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20mercury%20could%20sink%20tens%20of%20degrees%20below%20seasonal%20norms%20down%20to%20the%20US%20Gulf%20Coast.%20Before%20then%2C%20severe%20thunderstorms%20are%20expected%20across%20the%20lower%20Mississippi%20Valley%2C%20the%20NWS%20forecast.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3ETravel%20Disruptions%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20major%20storm%20of%202025%20was%20already%20wreaking%20havoc%20on%20travel%2C%20with%20Kansas%20City%20International%20Airport%20announcing%20the%20closure%20of%20its%20flight%20operations%20Saturday%20%26quot%3Bdue%20to%20rapid%20ice%20accumulation.%26quot%3B%20Flight%20operations%20resumed%20later%20after%20airfield%20runways%20and%20taxiways%20were%20treated%2C%20Kansas%20City%20mayor%20Quinton%20Lucas%20said%20in%20a%20social%20media%20post.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EParts%20of%20the%20eastern%20states%20of%20New%20York%20and%20Pennsylvania%20are%20facing%20%26quot%3Bheavy%20lake-effect%20snow%26quot%3B%20coming%20off%20the%20Great%20Lakes%20that%20could%20dump%20as%20much%20as%20two%20feet%20(61%20centimetres)%20there%2C%20according%20to%20the%20NWS.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EForecast%20company%20AccuWeather%20said%20Saturday%20that%20the%20lake-effect%20snow%20total%20in%20the%20region%2C%20already%20blanketed%20in%20snow%20this%20week%2C%20could%20top%20four%20feet.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20blizzard%20will%20rage%20across%20the%20Central%20Plains%20by%20early%20Sunday%2C%20and%20%26quot%3Bwhiteout%20conditions%20will%20make%20travel%20extremely%20hazardous%2C%20with%20impassable%20roads%20and%20a%20high%20risk%20of%20motorists%20becoming%20stranded%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20NWS%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20capital%20Washington%20could%20also%20be%20blanketed%20in%20five%20inches%20or%20more%20of%20snow%2C%20with%20up%20to%2010%20inches%20possible%20in%20nearby%20areas.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20major%20concern%20is%20freezing%20rain%20and%20sleet%20expected%20from%20Kansas%20eastward%20to%20Kentucky%20and%20Virginia%2C%20setting%20the%20stage%20for%20thick%20ice%20to%20coat%20roads%2C%20making%20travel%20hazardous%2C%20bringing%20down%20trees%