5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJustin%20Baldoni's%20libel%20lawsuit%3C%2Fa%3E%20against%20The%20New%20York%20Times%20may%20be%20tough%20to%20win%20but%20could%20help%20him%20in%20the%20court%20of%20public%20opinion%2C%20media%20lawyers%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBaldoni%20was%20part%20of%20a%20group%20that%20sued%20the%20Times%20this%20week%20over%20its%20bombshell%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2024%2F12%2F21%2Fbusiness%2Fmedia%2Fblake-lively-justin-baldoni-it-ends-with-us.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estory%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20Blake%20Lively's%20sexual-harassment%20claims%20against%20him.%20Baldoni%20and%20Lively%20starred%20in%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fit-ends-with-us-blake-lively-controversy-became-box-office-hit-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIt%20Ends%20With%20Us%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20film%20that%20%3C%2Fa%3Edebuted%20in%20August.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20libel%20suit%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.documentcloud.org%2Fdocuments%2F25473284-bi-https-media%2F%3F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccused%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20Times%20of%20relying%20%26quot%3Balmost%20entirely%26quot%3B%20on%20what%20it%20described%20as%20%26quot%3BLively's%20unverified%20and%20self-serving%20narrative%26quot%3B%20and%20said%20the%20newspaper%20disregarded%20%26quot%3Ban%20abundance%20of%20evidence%20that%20contradicted%20her%20claims%20and%20exposed%20her%20true%20motives%26quot%3B%20in%20its%20December%2021%20story.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20bar%20for%20someone%20considered%20a%20public%20figure%2C%20like%20Baldoni%2C%20to%20prove%20libel%20is%20high.%20Public%20figures%20have%20to%20show%20that%20a%20news%20outlet%20not%20only%20published%20false%20information%20but%20also%20knew%20it%20was%20false%20or%20had%20a%20reckless%20disregard%20for%20the%20truth%2C%20a%20standard%20called%20%26quot%3Bactual%20malice.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20suit%20against%20the%20paper%20is%20going%20to%20be%20an%20uphill%20battle%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Desir%C3%A9e%20Moore%2C%20a%20partner%20at%20Venable%20LLP%20who%20specializes%20in%20similar%20disputes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Times%20said%20in%20a%20statement%20that%20its%20story%20was%20%26quot%3Bmeticulously%20and%20responsibly%20reported%26quot%3B%20and%20that%20it%20planned%20to%20vigorously%20defend%20against%20the%20suit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20jurisdictions%20offer%20broad%20protections%20for%20news%20outlets%20to%20publish%20accusations%20that%20are%20deemed%20newsworthy%20and%20also%20part%20of%20official%20proceedings%20%E2%80%94%20even%20if%20they%20know%20those%20accusations%20are%20false.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Times%20article%20was%20largely%20based%20on%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2Finteractive%2F2024%2F12%2F21%2Fus%2Fcomplaint-of-blake-lively-v-wayfarer-studios-llc-et-al.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECalifornia%20Civil%20Rights%20Department%20complaint%3C%2Fa%3E%20(CRD)%20that%20Lively%20filed%2C%20which%20would%20be%20considered%20official%20proceedings.%20It%20included%20excerpts%20from%20text%20messages%20and%20emails%20that%20the%20CRD%20said%20she%20obtained%20through%20a%20subpoena.%20Several%20media%20lawyers%20told%20BI%20that%20this%20could%20help%20insulate%20the%20Times.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%26quot%3Bfair%20report%20privilege%26quot%3B%20in%20New%20York%2C%20where%20the%20libel%20suit%20was%20filed%2C%20protects%20the%20news%20media%20from%20defamation%20lawsuits%20when%20they%20publish%20accurate%20and%20fair%20reports%20of%20official%20proceedings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20public%20policy%20behind%20this%20privilege%20is%20that%20keeping%20citizens%20informed%20about%20matters%20of%20public%20concern%20is%20more%20important%20than%20protecting%20individual%20reputations%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Sean%20Andrade%2C%20a%20Los%20Angeles%20lawyer%20who's%20represented%20plaintiffs%20in%20libel%20cases.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22LOS%20ANGELES%2C%20CALIFORNIA%20-%20DECEMBER%2004%3A%20Justin%20Baldoni%20attends%20Variety%20Faith%20And%20Spirituality%20In%20Entertainment%20Honors%20presented%20by%20CFAM%20at%20Four%20Seasons%20Hotel%20Los%20Angeles%20at%20Beverly%20Hills%20on%20December%2004%2C%202024%20in%20Los%20Angeles%2C%20California.%20(Photo%20by%20Araya%20Doheny%2FVariety%20via%20Getty%20Images)%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F677863519de00e389eb45ac1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJustin%20Baldoni.%3Cp%3EAraya%20Doheny%2FVariety%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%220138b752-3eac-4476-a2d0-e9bfd000aa2a%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EBaldoni%20accused%20the%20Times%20of%20falsely%20attaching%20him%20to%20a%20smear%20campaign%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBaldoni's%20libel%20suit%20claimed%20that%20the%20Times%20falsely%20accused%20him%20of%20a%20campaign%20to%20smear%20Lively%20by%20cherry-picking%20the%20messages%20it%20reported.%20The%20suit%20said%20the%20Times%20knew%20its%20portrayal%20of%20him%20and%20the%20other%20plaintiffs%20was%20%26quot%3Bfalse%2C%20incomplete%2C%20misleading%2C%20and%20highly%20inflammatory.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20libel%20suit%20claimed%2C%20for%20example%2C%20that%20the%20Times'%20reporting%20on%20a%20text%20exchange%20between%20Baldoni's%20publicists%20Melissa%20Nathan%20and%20Jennifer%20Abel%20omitted%20the%20use%20of%20an%20upside-down%20smiley%20face%20emoji%20that%20indicated%20sarcasm.%20The%20Times%20said%20in%20a%20statement%20to%20BI%20that%20its%20reporters%20didn't%20see%20the%20emoji%20in%20question%20in%20the%20version%20of%20the%20docs%20they%20reviewed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20Times%20took%20certain%20texts%20out%20of%20context%2C%20that%20would%20be%20%26quot%3Ba%20little%20unethical%2C%26quot%3B%20Andrade%20said.%20But%2C%20in%20his%20view%2C%20that%20alone%20wouldn't%20negate%20that%20Baldoni's%20reps%20engaged%20in%20an%20alleged%20smear%20campaign.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBaldoni's%20libel%20suit%20also%20claimed%20that%20the%20Times%20made%20a%20false%20promise%20by%20publishing%20its%20article%20about%20two%20hours%20before%20the%20deadline%20it%20gave%20him%20and%20others%20to%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Times%20said%20in%20a%20statement%20to%20BI%20that%20the%20outlet%20shared%20the%20information%20it%20planned%20to%20publish%20with%20Baldoni%2C%20his%20production%20company%20Wayfarer%20Studios%2C%20and%20other%20subjects%20of%20the%20article%2C%20and%20that%20they%20chose%20not%20to%20talk%20to%20the%20Times%20or%20address%20any%20specifics.%20Instead%2C%20the%20Times%20said%2C%20the%20subjects%20emailed%20a%20joint%20statement%2C%20which%20the%20Times%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2Finteractive%2F2024%2F12%2F21%2Fus%2Fstatement-to-the-new-york-times.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eprinted%20in%20full%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAndrade%20felt%20that%20while%20it%20might%20be%20fair%20to%20point%20out%20that%20the%20Times%20didn't%20provide%20enough%20time%20to%20respond%2C%20as%20the%20libel%20suit%20claimed%2C%20that%20doesn't%20necessarily%20make%20the%20story%20libelous.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c0431b9a-b12e-4ddd-abee-8058c643e497%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EBaldoni's%20libel%20suit%20could%20have%20aims%20other%20than%20victory%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221440%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Blake%20Lively%20in%20%26quot%3BIt%20Ends%20With%20Us.%26quot%3B%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F677863d29de00e389eb45ade%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221080%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EBlake%20Lively%20in%20%26quot%3BIt%20Ends%20With%20Us.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3ESony%20Pictures%20Entertainment%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EMedia%20lawyers%20said%20that%20whether%20or%20not%20Baldoni%20prevails%20in%20court%2C%